r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-23_"><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-24_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-26_">Image by furmanphoto via Envato Elements</span></p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-7c8e" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-dBFCZX khzvmY pf-27_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-gvPcJq dRaLso"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-28_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:8px;--s-sm:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-29_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-30_">Celebrating activism and social change in the UK</h2><p class="sc-bhqpXc fHzOVK pf-32_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-8e790f7a-c83b-4f4f-a39a-e27752289971"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Every June, communities around the world come together to honour the resilience, visibility, and history of LGBTQ+ individuals during Pride Month. In the United Kingdom, Pride Month 2025 is being celebrated under the bold and timely theme: “<em>Activism and social change.</em>” This theme is not only a tribute to the trailblazers who have fought for LGBTQ+ rights throughout history, but also a call to action for everyone to continue building a more inclusive and equitable future.y.
<br>
</span></p><p class="sc-bhqpXc fHzOVK pf-35_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-ab212374-9823-4708-b3e7-8c5a085620bd"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">As colourful parades and community events take place across the UK, we are reminded that Pride is not only a celebration - it is a movement. A movement grounded in courage, love, and a relentless commitment to equality.
<br>
</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-38_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-39_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-40_">Why “<em>Activism and social change</em>” matters</h2><p class="sc-bhqpXc fHzOVK pf-42_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-4fa39ae2-7752-4899-b17f-c16c8e7f3a0d"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">The 2025 theme echoes a fundamental truth: LGBTQ+ rights have always been won through activism. From the Stonewall Uprising of 1969 to the legalisation of same-sex marriage in the UK in 2014, every stride toward equality has come through collective resistance, advocacy, and unwavering solidarity.
<br></span></p><p class="sc-bhqpXc fHzOVK pf-45_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-39eb3ce3-5663-4671-85c6-5d892a267a69"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">However, even in 2025, the work is far from over.
</span></p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-48_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-49_">LGBTQ+ youth are still disproportionately affected by mental health issues and bullying in schools.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-51_">Trans and non-binary individuals continue to face systemic barriers to healthcare, legal recognition, and workplace inclusion.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-53_">Hate crimes based on sexual orientation and gender identity remain prevalent in many parts of the UK.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-55_">Many workplaces lack comprehensive training on LGBTQ+ inclusion and equality.
</li></ul><p class="sc-bhqpXc fHzOVK pf-57_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-71c7822a-30ec-4024-9f8d-6c26c60f3350"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">In light of these realities, “<em>Activism and social change</em>” is more than a slogan - it is a demand for transformation in policies, institutions, and social attitudes. This theme urges individuals, communities, and organisations to move beyond performative gestures and into meaningful action.
</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-60_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-61_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-62_">UK-wide <em>‘Pride’</em> observance</h2><p class="sc-bhqpXc fHzOVK pf-64_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-15678291-3774-4862-89ed-30d8b5666bef"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">The UK joins the global community in celebrating Pride Month throughout June. A wide range of organisations, from advocacy groups and charities to local councils and corporate partners, are running events, campaigns, and educational programmes in honour of Pride. These efforts aim to promote awareness, inclusivity, and respect for the LGBTQ+ community.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-67_">Key events:</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-69_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-70_"><strong>Pride in London</strong> - 5 July, 2025</li></ul><p class="sc-bhqpXc fHzOVK pf-72_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-c8b42aeb-bebb-4ac1-b874-c3abdbccd6e6"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">The country’s largest LGBTQ+ event, themed <strong><em>“Embracing every shade: Celebrating diversity together”</em></strong>, features a vibrant parade, performances, panel discussions, and inclusive community engagement. Organised by Pride in London CIC, this flagship event attracts hundreds of thousands of supporters and is a vital space for visibility and activism.</span></p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-75_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-76_"><strong>Pride Cymru</strong> (Cardiff), <strong>Pride Canterbury</strong>, and others</li></ul><p class="sc-bhqpXc fHzOVK pf-78_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-0e12fec1-77f7-45fc-a0ab-bcab7d2f3735"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Regional celebrations take place across the country, each showcasing the unique voices, needs, and stories of local LGBTQ+ communities. These events serve as safe, joyful, and affirming spaces for LGBTQ+ individuals and allies to connect, celebrate, and advocate.</span></p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-81_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-82_"><strong>Educational campaigns</strong></li></ul><p class="sc-bhqpXc fHzOVK pf-84_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-0d7d4167-131a-4e05-b58d-ab2ff456f0d9"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Schools, universities, and workplaces are hosting webinars, workshops, and cultural events focusing on LGBTQ+ rights, inclusive language, mental health, and the history of Pride.</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-87_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-88_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-89_">How you can get involved this Pride Month</h2><p class="sc-bhqpXc fHzOVK pf-91_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-59c41b28-aa8b-4fea-bd48-07684e71a224"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">No matter your role - employer, educator, student, community member, or ally - you can be part of this movement for social change.
<br></span></p><p class="sc-bhqpXc fHzOVK pf-94_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-27bec638-3841-4c76-9c04-a5defcf05a2a"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Here’s how:
</span></p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-97_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-98_">Educate yourself and others about LGBTQ+ history, terminology, and intersectionality.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-100_">Host conversations in your workplace or school to unpack bias and build inclusion.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-102_">Support trans rights, advocate for inclusive healthcare, and amplify the voices of marginalised individuals.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-104_">Join your local Pride event to show solidarity and celebrate the diversity of the LGBTQ+ community.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-106_">Review your organisation’s DEI policies and embed inclusive practices.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-108_">Donate to or volunteer with LGBTQ+ charities and advocacy groups.
</li></ul><p class="sc-bhqpXc fHzOVK pf-110_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-39e06a80-80e6-48e0-b3ea-55f86b7881a5"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Every action, no matter how small, contributes to a future where everyone can live freely, authentically, and safely.
</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-113_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-114_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-115_">Conclusion</h2><p class="sc-bhqpXc fHzOVK pf-117_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-a1fd80fb-0774-4318-9c14-51d6b3539c1b"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">As we mark Pride Month 2025, we honour the boldness of those who came before us, the resilience of LGBTQ+ individuals today, and the hope of a brighter, more inclusive tomorrow. The theme “<em>Activism and social change</em>” reminds us that equality is not guaranteed - it is built through collective effort, courage, and compassion.<br>
</span></p><p class="sc-bhqpXc fHzOVK pf-120_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-9b0ecede-b5ee-4757-a9c0-93659738742c"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Let us move forward - not just with celebration, but with commitment. Let this Pride Month be a turning point where awareness becomes action, and visibility leads to systemic change.
<br>
</span></p><h4 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-123_">The role of organisations - Driving lasting change
</h4><p class="sc-bhqpXc fHzOVK pf-125_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-743318dc-1451-46b3-939c-1b461d2ae1d9"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">At <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/" target="_blank"><em><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);">The Mandatory Training Group</span></em></a>, we recognise that true inclusion goes beyond rainbow flags. Our work focuses on supporting organisations to create safe, respectful, and inclusive environments through robust training, governance, and compliance strategies.<br>
</span></p><p class="sc-bhqpXc fHzOVK pf-128_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-45506314-d2c2-4f58-b375-93aaedc91192"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Through our industry-leading <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/complyplus-regulatory-compliance-management-software" target="_blank"><em><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);">ComplyPlus™</span></em></a>, we help employers to:
<br>
</span></p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-131_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-132_">Implement inclusive policies aligned with the Equality Act 2010
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-134_">Deliver eLearning on unconscious bias, LGBTQ+ rights, and dignity at work
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-136_">Monitor Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion (DEI) performance across teams
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-138_">Promote a workplace culture rooted in psychological safety and belonging.
</li></ul><p class="sc-bhqpXc fHzOVK pf-140_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-8209cac5-e1f6-49d1-9dd5-82d22096a31d"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Creating an LGBTQ+ inclusive workplace is not a one-time initiative - it is an ongoing journey that demands intentionality, education, and accountability. Pride Month is an ideal time to renew your commitment and take meaningful steps toward progress.
</span></p><p class="sc-bhqpXc fHzOVK pf-143_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-dc1451d6-b353-4c1b-861d-2ae1d94b5477"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content "><em><strong>Last updated on 16-06-2025</strong></em></span></p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-9c13" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-dBFCZX khzvmY pf-146_ pf-color-scheme-1"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-gvPcJq dRaLso"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-147_ pf-r pf-c-cm" style="--s-xs:0px;--s-sm:15px;--s-lg:0px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-148_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-149_ pf-heading-1-h3 _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-151_">About the author
